of how to improve them.

254
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,310
There are thousands of YouTube videos

255
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:08,040
where experts teach you what
you need to know for free.

256
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:10,980
For example, if
communication is a weak spot,

257
00:10:10,980 --> 00:10:14,094
then there are videos on public
speaking and storytelling

258
00:10:14,094 --> 00:10:16,530
that you can take full advantage of.

259
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:18,750
Now, learning high value skills

260
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:20,790
does more than just paying the bills.

261
00:10:20,790 --> 00:10:22,890
They compound into every aspect

262
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:25,290
of your business and social life.

263
00:10:25,290 --> 00:10:27,150
I used to find what they taught in school

264
00:10:27,150 --> 00:10:29,670
to be boring and nonsensical.

265
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:32,640
With my goals and vision,
it just didn't make sense

266
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,975
for me to waste my time
learning about algebra

267
00:10:34,975 --> 00:10:37,380
and other things, so I went out

268
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:39,750
and bought my own books about business.

269
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,935
I used all my free time to teach myself

270
00:10:41,935 --> 00:10:45,390
all the basics of how to
start and run a company.

271
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:48,240
I then combined everything
I learned with my passion

272
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:51,480
for RC models and started my own company,

273
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,370
which went on to make millions

274
00:10:53,370 --> 00:10:55,710
and make me the man I am today.

275
00:10:55,710 --> 00:10:57,540
- Tip six, build a credit score.

276
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:59,280
If you haven't got a trust fund,

277
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:01,470
then you are gonna need
to leverage good debt

278
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:04,170
in order to become a
millionaire at a young age.

279
00:11:04,170 --> 00:11:05,970
And without a good credit score,

280
00:11:05,970 --> 00:11:07,830
that's gonna be near impossible.

281
00:11:07,830 --> 00:11:10,477
I was told when I was
younger, this famous saying

282
00:11:10,477 --> 00:11:12,810
"Never a borrower or a lender be,"

283
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:14,460
which is completely wrong.

284
00:11:14,460 --> 00:11:17,400
I have a feeling this was
made up by powerful people

285
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:21,180
years ago to stop you
leveraging your way to success.

286
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:23,160
Borrowing money can be
one of the best ways

287
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:26,088
to elevate yourself past
your born class status.

288
00:11:26,088 --> 00:11:28,020
But due to my fear of debt,

289
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:29,880
I never really took advantage of it.

290
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,800
This is a personal regret of mine

291
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,860
and I wish I'd borrowed
more when I was younger.

292
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:36,210
It really could have helped me

293
00:11:36,210 --> 00:11:38,700
leverage my wealth much faster.

294
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,020
Now, this isn't for everyone

295
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:42,660
and takes a strong clear mind to manage,

296
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:45,390
but can work extremely
well if done correctly.

297
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:47,310
A credit score is basically a trust

298
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:49,018
and reliability rating used by banks

299
00:11:49,018 --> 00:11:51,630
to judge the risk of lending you money.

300
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:52,950
Think of it like this.

301
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:55,800
If every time your mate
lends you five bucks,

302
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:59,490
and you give it back when or
before you said you would,

303
00:11:59,490 --> 00:12:01,860
then there's a much bigger
chance that your mate's

304
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:04,770
gonna lend you a hundred
dollars if you ever need it

305
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:05,970
because he can trust you.

306
00:12:05,970 --> 00:12:08,250
A good credit score is priceless.

307
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,930
It will take years to build,

308
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:12,540
but you can lose it in
just one wrong move.

309
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:16,170
By taking on debt responsibly
and paying it off on time,

310
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:18,510
you can build a positive credit history

311
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:20,550
which can open up more opportunities

312
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:21,930
for credit in the future.

313
00:12:21,930 --> 00:12:24,990
Now, you might be thinking,
where do I even begin?

314
00:12:24,990 --> 00:12:26,640
Well start small of course.

315
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:29,310
At a young age, you can't
just wander into a bank

316
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:31,200
and start borrowing heaps of cash,

317
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,090
but you may already be paying bills

318
00:12:33,090 --> 00:12:35,250
that will count towards
your credit rating,

319
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,620
such as a phone contract in your name.

320
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:39,270
As soon as you turn 18,

321
00:12:39,270 --> 00:12:41,790
make sure to grab yourself a credit card.

322
00:12:41,790 --> 00:12:43,200
If that's gonna be a while,

323
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,360
then you could become an authorized user

324
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,950
on your parents' credit card.

325
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:50,070
Either route you take, remember
these three simple rules.

326
00:12:50,070 --> 00:12:52,350
First, make on time payments.

327
00:12:52,350 --> 00:12:54,240
Paying your bills on time is the single,

328
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:57,150
most critical factor in
building a good credit score.

329
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,800
In short, don't be late.

330
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,499
Second, keep your credit utilization low.

331
00:13:01,499 --> 00:13:04,740
Credit utilization is
simply the amount of credit

332
00:13:04,740 --> 00:13:07,890
you are using compared to the
amount you have available.

333
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:12,210
As a tip, when starting
out, stay below 30%,

334
00:13:12,210 --> 00:13:14,310
essentially don't spend it all.

335
00:13:14,310 --> 00:13:17,100
Third, don't apply for too much credit.

336
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:19,560
This can be interpreted as desperation

337
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:21,810
and lower your score significantly.

338
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:23,940
Remember, less is more.

339
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:25,050
If you follow these rules,

340
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:26,760
then you'll certainly
be in a good position

341
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:29,340
to start growing your
wealth at a rapid rate.

342
00:13:29,340 --> 00:13:31,830
Tip seven, follow the money.

343
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:35,550
In life, doing what you love
won't always make you rich.

344
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:38,340
While it's important to pursue
what you love and enjoy,

345
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:40,470
it's also essential to
balance your passions

346
00:13:40,470 --> 00:13:41,700
with practicality.

347
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:42,810
If you have a passion,

348
00:13:42,810 --> 00:13:45,690
but don't think it'll
pay you, flip the script.

349
00:13:45,690 --> 00:13:47,910
A good example of someone
doing exactly this

350
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:50,430
is Rick Shiels, who we
recently interviewed

351
00:13:50,430 --> 00:13:52,290
on our podcast, "Strike It Big."

352
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:55,050
His ambition was to become
a professional golfer

353
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:56,640
on the PGA tour.

354
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:59,460
However, although he was
very good in his youth,

355
00:13:59,460 --> 00:14:02,070
and to be honest he still is to this day,

356
00:14:02,070 --> 00:14:04,080
he knew he wouldn't make the cut.

357
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:06,060
Therefore, he flipped the script

358
00:14:06,060 --> 00:14:08,310
and combined his natural talent for golf

359
00:14:08,310 --> 00:14:11,280
with his passion for drama and technology.

360
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:14,550
This led to him starting a
YouTube channel coaching others

361
00:14:14,550 --> 00:14:17,190
and now he's the most subscribed golfer

362
00:14:17,190 --> 00:14:20,070
in the entire world,
earning millions per year.

363
00:14:20,070 --> 00:14:22,170
Building on this, my son Curtis

364
00:14:22,170 --> 00:14:24,360
was passionate about making videos.

365
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:26,130
He was making YouTube videos,

366
00:14:26,130 --> 00:14:28,770
but realized it wasn't
gonna be successful.

367
00:14:28,770 --> 00:14:31,440
So he pivoted to making commercial films

368
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:34,110
for nightclubs, weddings, advertisements

369
00:14:34,110 --> 00:14:36,810
and anything in between,
he'd take any job.

370
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,730
Then he followed the money and niched down

371
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:40,560
into the business coaching space

372
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:42,780
as he enjoyed working with these clients

373
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:45,420
as those were the videos
that made the most money.

374
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:47,160
He's now my business partner

375
00:14:47,160 --> 00:14:49,110
in this very channel you are watching

376
00:14:49,110 --> 00:14:51,510
and these videos wouldn't
be possible without him.

377
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:54,750
So he's involved in something
he loves, making good money,

378
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:57,300
but it's not in the way
he originally intended.

379
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:59,190
Both examples here followed the money

380
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:01,710
and flipped the script
to work in their favor

381
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:02,940
and you can do this too.

382
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:05,670
It's crucial to learn
skills that are in demand.

383
00:15:05,670 --> 00:15:08,790
Identify industries and
professions that are thriving

384
00:15:08,790 --> 00:15:11,370
and have a future and
invest time and effort

385
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:13,620
in learning the skills that can help you

386
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:15,660
succeed in those areas.

387
00:15:15,660 --> 00:15:17,430
Tip eight, become a quitter.

388
00:15:17,430 --> 00:15:20,342
You need to get good at quitting
or you'll never succeed.

389
00:15:20,342 --> 00:15:23,100
Imagine you are at a
cinema and you've paid

390
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:26,250
for your ticket and you sit
down to watch the movie.

391
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:30,300
About 10 minutes in, you realize
that it's absolute rubbish.

392
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:33,660
It's so boring that a two
hour chat with your granddad

393
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:36,210
about his childhood dog
would be more stimulating.

394
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:38,370
But instead of leaving
and doing something else,

395
00:15:38,370 --> 00:15:40,440
you decide to stay and
watch the whole thing

396
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,540
because you feel like you've already paid

397
00:15:42,540 --> 00:15:43,890
and you don't wanna waste your money.

398
00:15:43,890 --> 00:15:46,290
This is an example of sunk cost fallacy.

399
00:15:46,290 --> 00:15:49,200
The money you paid for your
ticket, it's already spent

400
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,900
and it can't be refunded,
so whether you stay

401
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,810
for the whole movie or leave
early, the money's gone.

402
00:15:54,810 --> 00:15:58,140
It will be better to cut
your losses and leave early

403
00:15:58,140 --> 00:15:59,790
if you're not enjoying the movie,

404
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:01,530
rather than sticking around or wasting

405
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:04,650
more time and energy on
something you don't like

406
00:16:04,650 --> 00:16:07,350
just because you feel like
you've already invested in it.

407
00:16:07,350 --> 00:16:10,410
The same thing can happen
in other areas of your life.

408
00:16:10,410 --> 00:16:12,900
Maybe you've invested a lot of time, money

409
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:16,410
or effort into a project
that isn't working out,

410
00:16:16,410 --> 00:16:18,630
but you keep going just
because you feel like

411
00:16:18,630 --> 00:16:20,760
you've already put so much in.

412
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,590
But just like the movie ticket,

413
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:26,130
the resources you've already
invested are a sunk cost.

414
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:27,360
You can't get them back.

415
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:29,070
It's better to cut your losses

416
00:16:29,070 --> 00:16:30,810
and move on to something else

417
00:16:30,810 --> 00:16:33,510
rather than sticking around
and wasting more resources

418
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:36,000
on something that just isn't working.

419
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,190
Let's be honest, making your first million

420
00:16:38,190 --> 00:16:41,160
is never going to be easy,
but it can be simple.

421
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:44,160
If you are young, use
time to your advantage.

422
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,810
I made millions while I was young

423
00:16:45,810 --> 00:16:47,820
and also built generational wealth

424
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:49,530
by investing for the long term.

425
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:50,970
Don't listen to anyone that tells you

426
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:53,370
that you have to pick one lane.

427
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:55,500
You can do both at the same time.

428
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:57,810
If you want to know some
great ways to make money

429
00:16:57,810 --> 00:16:59,610
with your phone as a teenager,

430
00:16:59,610 --> 00:17:01,680
then I'll leave that video right up there

431
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:03,240
but don't click on it just yet.

432
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:05,880
Remember to subscribe if you
want to grow your wealth.

433
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:07,983
Okay, I'll see you over there.

